<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Demo OAuth2 Client</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

    <!-- jQuery (necessary for Bootstrap's JavaScript plugins) -->
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.1.1.min.js"></script>
    <!-- material design lite -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/materialize/0.98.1/css/materialize.min.css">
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/materialize/0.98.1/js/materialize.min.js"></script>

</head>
<!--<body style="background-color:#eee;">-->
<body>

<nav class="orange" role="navigation">
    <div class="nav-wrapper container">
        <a id="logo-container" href="#" class="brand-logo">OAuth 2 Client</a>

        <ul id="nav-mobile" class="right hide-on-med-and-down">
            <li><a href="/auth_code">AO Password</a></li>
            <li><a href="/auth_code">RO Password</a></li>
            <li><a href="/implicit">Implicit Password</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</nav>

<div class="container">

    <!-- Page Content goes here -->
    <div class="row">

        <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="card blue-grey darken-1">
                <div class="card-content white-text">
                    <span class="card-title">Authorization Code Flow</span>
                    <p>Authorization Code provides a safe way to communicate between
                        the authorization server and the client server. The access
                        token will only be revealed to the client server.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card-action">
                    <a href="/auth_code" class="">
                        Try now
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="card blue-grey darken-1">
                <div class="card-content white-text">
                    <span class="card-title">Resource Owner Password Flow</span>
                    <p>Resource Owner Password flow allows a login by transmitting
                        username and password from the page - typically by using a
                        script. Thus it can integrate very well into an existing design.
                        The access token will not be directly visible to the client
                        server.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card-action">
                    <a href="/auth_code" class="">
                        Try now
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="card blue-grey darken-1">
                <div class="card-content white-text">
                    <span class="card-title">Implicit Grant Flow</span>
                    <p>Implicit client flow puts the access token directly in the
                        url of callback redirect. The access token can be read by javascript
                        on the page.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card-action">
                    <a href="/implicit" class="">
                        Try now
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>